<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PAY RAISE FOR NON-TEACHERS APPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Non-teaching employees in the Inglewood Unified School District will receive 
the same salary increase as teachers under a tentative agreement reached this 
week. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement, approved by the school board Wednesday night, calls for a 
retroactive 2% salary increase for last school year and 5.4% for the current 
year, which ends June 30. The contract for the 1990-91 school year is still up 
for negotiation. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement will become final if approved by members of California 
Professional Education Employees on Wednesday. 
</P>
