<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. SCHOOL BOARD REJECTS STIFFER PENALTY ON WEAPONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Insanity seems to prevail in the school board decision not to automatically 
expel students armed with lethal weapons on campus. 
</P>
<P>
Your editorial "When Students Tote Guns, Not Books" (May 9) was equally 
outrageous. 
</P>
<P>
I quote ". . . without kicking out frightened youngsters who carry a Scout 
knife for protection against gangs and bullies." 
</P>
<P>
Thus the writer sees nothing wrong with a student carrying a Scout knife to use 
against those who threaten him at school. Who is to decide who the gang members 
and bullies are, each student? A Scout knife is a deadly weapon and is 
dangerous if used for self-protection. But it is really no match for a gun. I 
humbly suggest that the school board enact a new rule that all students can 
carry guns for protection. Of course, the teachers would be issued assault 
rifles to ensure fair play. Maybe the NRA could be talked into training the 
students in quick draw and accuracy. 
</P>
<P>
LEE L. BANDLE 
</P>
<P>
Palm Desert 
</P>
