<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDUCATION GOALS NEED TO BE RE-EXAMINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
You ran a story on declining college enrollments among qualified minority 
students. 
</P>
<P>
Your "experts" cited rising costs and admissions standards as the causes (" 'A' 
Students Resorting to Plan 'B'," May 20). 
</P>
<P>
Never once did the writer mention the existence of California's community 
colleges, which provide good, affordable education within easy commuting 
distance. 
</P>
<P>
Perhaps high schools should spend more time working with students on what is 
possible and available and less on talking and thinking only about UC. 
</P>
<P>
BARBARA S. STONE, trustee, Rio Hondo Community College District 
</P>
</TEXT>
