<HEADLINE>
<P>
DR. NEIL SOLOMON: BETA-CAROTENE SOURCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. NEIL SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: I have learned quite a bit about vitamins, minerals and other 
nutrients from your column, and my family's diet has improved considerably as a 
result. 
</P>
<P>
But now I've been reading about beta-carotene. Is it a vitamin? What foods is 
it found in? 
</P>
<P>
Answer: Beta-carotene is one of the carotenoids, a group of compounds related 
to Vitamin A. Beta-Carotene is found in deep-yellow and dark-green vegetables. 
</P>
</TEXT>
