<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anne Bogart Quits Trinity: Anne Bogart, artistic director of the Trinity 
Repertory Company in Providence, R.I., has resigned her post. 
</P>
<P>
Bogart and the Trinity Rep board clashed earlier this week about cuts in the 
proposed 1990-91 budgets. Bogart said any cuts would mean the termination of 
staff members and the backing off from commitments. When the board, which said 
the Rep's operating costs for the past few years were more than its box office 
and fund-raising revenues, insisted on the cuts, Bogart resigned. No 
replacement has been named. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
