<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: JOFFREY BOARD OKS DEAL FOR ARPINO'S RETURN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Joffrey Ballet board on Thursday ratified the agreement that will lead to 
the return of Gerald Arpino as artistic director of the company, and announced 
that a 10-member executive committee will "help run the company on a day-to-day 
basis." 
</P>
<P>
The agreement "resolves all outstanding issues" between Arpino and the company, 
according to a statement issued by the company, which is based in New York and 
Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Arpino has agreed to license his ballets to the company, the agreement said. 
</P>
<P>
The board did not specifically name the executive committee members, other than 
Arpino, but a spokesman said they will be "members of the board that will be 
drawn from both coasts." 
</P>
<P>
In the wake of a wave of resignations of top board members on both coasts, the 
board named as its new co-chairmen Los Angeles attorney Brad Brian and Carl 
Epstein, managing director of Halston Enterprises in New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
