<HEADLINE>
<P>
S.D. BALLET DIRECTOR HEADS FOR SOVIET UNION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Maxine Mahon of the California Ballet is headed for the Soviet Union at the 
invitation of the Ballet School in Tbilisi, Soviet Georgia. 
</P>
<P>
The director will attend a two-week course for dance teachers, scheduled to 
begin at the end of May. 
</P>
<P>
The trip will coincide with Cal Ballet student Calvin Kitten's graduation from 
an exchange program in Tbilisi, which will bring a Soviet dance student to the 
company's ranks in the fall. 
</P>
<P>
Mahon is planning side-trips to Moscow and other Soviet cities as well, to pave 
the way for a 1991-92 tour of the Soviet Union by her San Diego-based ballet 
troupe. 
</P>
<P>
Olga Smoak, an international dance agent, will accompany Mahon to the Soviet 
Union. 
</P>
