</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WRONG NUMBER: It happens in nearly every political campaign -- a mass mailing 
seeking support lands on the most inopportune doorstep. . . . This time, a 
strongly worded pitch for Assessor Bradley L. Jacobs, focusing on his battle 
with local cable television operators over increased taxes, went to two 
executives of companies which have filed suit against Jacobs. . . . His 
consultant, who said the volunteer envelope stuffers "don't read the paper," 
suggested the executives "can simply toss it." Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
