<P>
SCHOOL'S OUT: The proposal that three elementary schools be closed in 
Huntington Beach (B4) is nothing new for Orange County but may be the end of a 
trend. . . . Countywide figures are tough to come by, but nearly 40 schools 
have been closed in six of the county's 28 districts alone. The Westminster, 
Orange and Newport-Mesa districts have reopened or built new elementary schools 
and are contemplating more in the next two years. . . . Says Westminster 
Assistant Supt. Barbara Winars: "We're on the way back up." Mark I. Pinsky and 
Steve Emmons 
