objective for volunteers is to keep the animals happy and adoptable. ; Photo, 
At left, Sue Nelson and dog embark on a jaunt. Above, Nelson offers some 
tenderness. "Without the volunteer help, we would not be able to keep up the 
shelter as we do now," manager Roberta Gorny said. ; Photo, Volunteers' duties 
include walking and bathing the dogs and taking them to the veterinarian. They 
are also trained to issue licenses. MARK BOSTER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
