<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN WHO KILLED 2 STUDIO GUARDS IS RULED INSANE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former mental patient today was found innocent by reason of insanity in the 
fatal shootings of two Universal Studios guards, in a plea bargain that 
prosecutors say will keep him hospitalized for the rest of his life. 
</P>
<P>
Nathan Nicholas Trupp, 43, said he understood the terms of his plea and 
acknowledged that he killed guards Jeren Beeks and Armando Torres in a violent 
attack at a Universal Studios gate on Dec. 1, 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Trupp, who was sought by New Mexico authorities for investigation of killing 
three people in Albuquerque a few days earlier, went to the studio in search of 
actor Michael Landon. 
</P>
<P>
As the slender, bearded Trupp entered his pleas, the families of the two 
victims sat sobbing in the spectator section of the court. Two of them said 
outside they were pleased that Trupp was now unable to harm anyone else. 
</P>
</TEXT>
