<TEXT>
<P>
An Air Force fighter jet crashed into a residential area today, setting two 
homes ablaze and killing the pilot and a housekeeper, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The F-16A was on a training flight from Moody Air Force Base near Valdosta to 
Lake George Weapons Range in Florida when it crashed in southern Georgia, Moody 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The pilot was the only one aboard, public affairs officer Dee Tait said. Names 
of the dead were not immediately released. 
</P>
<P>
Parts of the plane hit Mary Alice Corbitt's home. Corbitt "was in the middle 
bedroom and heard a loud noise, a boom. The debris hit the house and debris 
came in. There was fire inside the house," said her daughter-in-law, who said 
Corbitt was too upset to speak on the telephone. 
</P>
<P>
"It was very loud -- almost like a sonic boom," said David McDonald, assistant 
principal at Atkinson County High School, about half a mile from the site. "It 
shook real hard." 
</P>
