you wanted to be the hero, the prince, the king . . . Now you're the prince of 
the news." Rather recalled planting trees in front of the school during an 
Arbor Day celebration. "I take more sheer pride in planting those trees than 
almost anything else," he said. Rather gave the students a few inspirational 
words, urging them to study hard even though he admitted, "I can't tell you I 
always did that when I was here." 
