<P>
CLINTON SEIZED ON COCAINE COUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
George Clinton, leader of the funk bands Parliament and the Funkadelics, faces 
cocaine charges after his arrest in Los Angeles early today. 
</P>
<P>
Clinton, 45, was a passenger in a car driven by Archie Ray Ivy, 39, when they 
were stopped because the car's headlights were not on. The officer discovered 
two packages of cocaine on the front seat and arrested both men. Clinton had 
been returning to his hotel with Ivy after a recording session. 
