</P>
<P>
INDY MINI-MARATHON RECORD SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
INDIANAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Milwaukee man won today's Indianapolis 500 Festival Mini-Marathon in record 
time in cool, rainy conditions. 
</P>
<P>
Keith Hanson's unofficial time was 1 hour, 4 minutes and 14 seconds, breaking 
the previous record by about 1.5 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
Ruth Ozmun won the women's division with an unofficial time of 1:18.19. Her 
hometown was not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
About 10,000 runners took the green flag at Monument Circle downtown at 9 a.m. 
and ran the more than 13-mile course to the Indianapolis Motor Speedway. 
</P>
<P>
Light rain and a temperature around 60 degrees proved to be the perfect 
combination for Hansen. 
</P>
<P>
"It made a difference," he said. "The temperature was great. It was nice to 
have a little rain to cool things off." 
</P>
</TEXT>
